Dialogue: 0,00:01:13.57,00:01:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Don't know how many times.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:01:14.99,00:01:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I've been crossed off the \Nlist and left for dead.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:01:19.20,00:01:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Guess when it first happens \Nthe day you were born,</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:01:22.92,00:01:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>you're gonna lose count.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:01:29.96,00:01:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>So this,</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:01:32.59,00:01:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>this ain't nothing new.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:10:54.49,00:10:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>There are bad days,</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:10:58.32,00:11:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>and then there are \Nlegendary bad days.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:03.29,00:11:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Whole damn planet \Nwanted a piece of me.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:10.38,00:11:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Can't stay in the open.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:14.34,00:11:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Can't risk another attack.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:36.32,00:11:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>It's always the punch you don't \Nsee coming that puts you down.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:43.62,00:11:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>But why didn't I see it?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:45.91,00:11:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>But why didn't I see it?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:51.71,00:11:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Of course they were \Ngonna try to kill me.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:54.30,00:11:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Death is what they \Ndo for a living.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:02.30,00:12:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>So the question ain't \N"What happened?".</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:05.39,00:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>The question is.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:09.35,00:12:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>"What happened to me?"</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:29.37,00:12:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the Lord Marshal now.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:32.79,00:12:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>How did they get so close?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:38.80,00:12:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>How did I let them \Nblindside me like that?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:42.47,00:12:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Threshold! \NTake us to the threshold!
Dialogue: 0,00:12:46.18,00:12:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Necromongers.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:48.85,00:12:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Some wanted to put a \Ncrown on my head.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:53.65,00:12:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Some wanted to put a \Nnoose around my neck.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:59.49,00:13:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Okay, more nooses than crowns.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:13:05.33,00:13:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I needed a way out.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:13:09.25,00:13:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Some new place.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:13:13.08,00:13:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Or maybe just an old one.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:13:21.47,00:13:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>But how do you find something \Nyou've never seen?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:13:37.77,00:13:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Making more friends, I see.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:40.78,00:13:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But who put her up to it?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:43.28,00:13:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Which commander?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:46.41,00:13:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be any of many.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:49.91,00:13:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't doubt it for a second,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:53.33,00:13:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander Vaako.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:56.50,00:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Marshal.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:06.89,00:14:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They say you lost \Nyour nerve, Vaako,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:10.56,00:14:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,after that big \Nswing and a miss.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:14.94,00:14:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what they say?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:20.57,00:14:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what are you gonna do \Nto get that cred back?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:24.95,00:14:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the big play?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:28.62,00:14:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Something splashy.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:35.04,00:14:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:37.21,00:14:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I had in mind \Nsomething different.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:47.51,00:14:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking about \Nan early campaign.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:52.10,00:14:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My very first. \NI was but a boy.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:56.48,00:14:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We dropped from the sky and \Ndid what Necromongers do.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:01.61,00:15:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Destruction was breathtaking.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:07.82,00:15:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we met resistance.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:11.28,00:15:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ferocious like a \Nstorm of lions.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:16.66,00:15:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of them killed \Nover a hundred Necro
Dialogue: 0,00:15:20.50,00:15:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,before their weapons failed.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:25.17,00:15:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they killed \Nanother 30 more.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:28.34,00:15:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Barehanded.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:32.10,00:15:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our firepower and \Nstrength in numbers
Dialogue: 0,00:15:35.14,00:15:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually won us the day.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:38.35,00:15:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can still see him, the last \Nof those magnificent warriors,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:42.77,00:15:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,standing on a pile of his own.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:47.20,00:15:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And he looked at me.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:52.45,00:15:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will never \Nforget those eyes.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:02.54,00:16:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,His eyes were just like yours.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:10.89,00:16:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The planet was Furya.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:14.60,00:16:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it's called.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:17.52,00:16:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't \Nknow where it is.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:20.10,00:16:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I need charts. I need maps.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:22.69,00:16:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Impossible. \N- I need a direction.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:24.52,00:16:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Purged from all records, \Nas you well know.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:26.73,00:16:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But you remember where.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:32.24,00:16:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So many worlds...
Dialogue: 0,00:16:35.66,00:16:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The only map left in existence
Dialogue: 0,00:16:38.08,00:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is the one that's in \Nmy head, Riddick.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:48.92,00:16:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:52.18,00:16:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The crown?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:58.60,00:17:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcendence.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:04.69,00:17:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Krone.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:06.90,00:17:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Break off a ship.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:10.11,00:17:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Riddick's going home.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:14.20,00:17:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Transcendence.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:16.95,00:17:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I guess that was Necro speak for "Get the \Nfuck off our ship and make it forever."</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:23.29,00:17:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Fine by me.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:29.38,00:17:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>You can't blame him \Nfor dangling Furya.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:33.47,00:17:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Home has a certain equity.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:38.77,00:17:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>But I do blame him \Nfor what came next.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:57.49,00:17:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's along way to come.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:00.45,00:18:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For this.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:03.29,00:18:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>This guy with the \Nfucked-up face, Krone,</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:07.29,00:18:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>he was supposed to \Nbe our ride home.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:12.09,00:18:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>But instead of Furya, we \Nwind up someplace called...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:18.22,00:18:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Not Furya.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:28.98,00:18:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Yet again, someone was \Ntrying to play me.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:34.65,00:18:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>So yet again,</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:38.62,00:18:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>we play for blood.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:12.54,00:20:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep what you \Nkill, Riddick!
Dialogue: 0,00:20:16.17,00:20:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep what you kill!
Dialogue: 0,00:20:24.01,00:20:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Somewhere along \Nthe way, I lost a step.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:27.64,00:20:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I got sloppy.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:30.06,00:20:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Dulled my own edge.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:33.90,00:20:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Maybe I went and did the \Nworst crime of all...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:38.61,00:20:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I got civilized.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:47.54,00:20:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>So now we zero the clock.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:52.25,00:20:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Just me and this \Nno-name world.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:20:58.42,00:21:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Gotta find that \Nanimal side again.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:22:37.10,00:22:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Before long, I realized there was \Na whole other world over there,</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:22:43.40,00:22:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>of water, grass and life.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:22:48.66,00:22:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Just had one thing in my way.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:24:03.73,00:24:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:51.86,00:26:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, show me some teeth.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:07.60,00:28:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Escape artist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:52.52,00:30:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What you got over there?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:06.53,00:31:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thought we shared everything.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:31.93,00:31:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop it.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:31.62,00:32:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:08.69,00:33:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bounty hunters.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:25.63,00:33:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:28.59,00:33:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:30.72,00:33:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Steady...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:33.09,00:33:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:40.31,00:33:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:44.86,00:33:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:50.99,00:33:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:54.20,00:33:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All yours.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:01.83,00:34:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It says "dog food" on it.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:05.04,00:34:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could read.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:12.22,00:34:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:19.51,00:34:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Bring \Nme my reserve.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:35.70,00:34:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's yours?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:06.81,00:35:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Rain.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:08.69,00:35:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:11.48,00:35:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because you've never seen it \Nbefore doesn't mean it's a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:15.82,00:35:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, easy.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:32.34,00:35:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like our \Ntime is up here.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:33.75,00:37:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:37.42,00:37:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Look again, Diaz.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:42.93,00:37:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody should teach this \NRiddick asshole how to count.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:46.22,00:37:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"Leave one ship"? Like we've got \Na fucking spare laying around.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:51.14,00:37:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's crank it up.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:03.66,00:38:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Cyclops.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:39.61,00:38:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit. Here comes \Nthe neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:48.66,00:38:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Small world.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:58.38,00:39:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Unidentified vessel, this is \NClan Vagos out of Ursa Five.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:02.51,00:39:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Be advised that we are \Non the ground now
Dialogue: 0,00:39:04.72,00:39:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and have responded to \Nan emergency signal.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:07.22,00:39:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No distress found, \Nno need to land.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:11.35,00:39:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I repeat, there is no reason for you \Nto land at this location at this time.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:16.44,00:39:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Is that clear?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:39:17.73,00:39:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>No reason for you to land at \Nthis location at this time.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:39:24.40,00:39:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck did I just say?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:44.09,00:39:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a long haul. We \Ncould take on some water.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:47.72,00:39:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't mind a little \Ntrue-gravity time either.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:50.60,00:39:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I was saying, \NI've got this.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:00.44,00:40:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew who that was, right? \NOn the emergency beacon?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:06.36,00:40:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't be here if I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:10.03,00:40:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The concept of back-up still \Nhas no appeal to you?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:12.87,00:40:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My besties here can \Nball with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:15.91,00:40:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No disrespect for \Nyour crew, of course,
Dialogue: 0,00:40:17.83,00:40:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who look strong, too, in \Nthose matchy-matchy outfits.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:22.96,00:40:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit. Didn't know there \Nwas a dress code.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:25.84,00:40:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:27.17,00:40:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not my intention \Nto jump another man's claim.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:30.84,00:40:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't mind, maybe \Nwe'll just pull up a chair
Dialogue: 0,00:40:32.51,00:40:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and spectate for a while.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:35.85,00:40:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I do?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:37.85,00:40:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a co-op station, \Npal. It's open to all Mercs.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:42.61,00:40:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- By the way, my name is... \N- "Too late."
Dialogue: 0,00:40:45.36,00:40:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your name. "Too Late."
Dialogue: 0,00:40:49.20,00:40:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't need you stepping all \Nover my dick here, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:52.99,00:40:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll tell you what.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:55.70,00:40:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't lift a finger to help until \Nyou come ask me for it. How's that?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:16.97,00:41:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was scoping \Nthis out earlier.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:19.02,00:41:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a cave system. \NFive clicks South.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:21.69,00:41:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Might be worth a look.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:24.19,00:41:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Too Late.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:26.32,00:41:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Need to pull a node \Nfrom your ship
Dialogue: 0,00:41:28.15,00:41:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and store it right here \Nnext to mine. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:29.90,00:41:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:31.49,00:41:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Riddick triggered the beacon \Nto get off-world, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:35.49,00:41:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, he was \Ncalling a taxi.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:41.33,00:41:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,00:41:43.08,00:41:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And a ship would make \Na sweet trap, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:46.00,00:41:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Confined space, metal \Nwalls, jail cell.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:51.38,00:41:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is cool, huh?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:52.84,00:41:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true half the \Npeople you meet
Dialogue: 0,00:41:54.59,00:41:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,are below average \Nintelligence?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:56.35,00:41:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to make sure the ship stays \Ngrounded when he comes for them, okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:59.18,00:42:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:01.35,00:42:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dahl, pull a node \Nfrom the ship.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:28.88,00:42:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it...
Dialogue: 0,00:42:30.05,00:42:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,00:42:31.17,00:42:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh...
Dialogue: 0,00:42:51.65,00:42:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Any time now, Riddick.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:17.34,00:43:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, this \Nis total overkill.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:19.43,00:43:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Eleven of \Nus out here now?
Dialogue: 0,00:43:21.81,00:43:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Should have been a \Nfour-man op, tops.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:24.56,00:43:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You are jinxing our janx, man. \NAnd that ain't cool.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:27.48,00:43:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I don't give a shit \Nwhat they say. He's one guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:33.23,00:43:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you say, man.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:35.78,00:43:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's one guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:40.78,00:43:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,00:43:52.75,00:43:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess that's what passes for \Na fucking moon on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:56.97,00:43:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna be a dark night.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:59.64,00:44:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Advantage, him.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:02.47,00:44:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's gonna wear you down first. \NForce you to go without sleep.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:06.60,00:44:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see I'm busy?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:09.44,00:44:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just sharing my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:11.61,00:44:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now that you have,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:15.99,00:44:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can I politely invite you to
Dialogue: 0,00:44:18.32,00:44:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,step off my fucking porch?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:23.45,00:44:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll start rotating down.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:25.45,00:44:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You let me know, huh?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:26.95,00:44:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as I have his head in \Na box, I will let you know.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:55.19,00:44:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Grid 29D. Stand by, stand by.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:02.49,00:45:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>What you got, cuz?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:45:05.99,00:45:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha, some dingo-dongo thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:13.04,00:45:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I see it now.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:16.00,00:45:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>You want me to pop it?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:45:17.17,00:45:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock it down. One \Nshot suppressed.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:24.80,00:45:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice work, Diaz. Encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:28.31,00:45:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Had something in my eye.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:30.44,00:45:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>It's called a scope.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:45:32.19,00:45:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Try next time.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:45:34.02,00:45:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>You got this, right?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:45:36.82,00:45:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you get off my \Nfreaking frequency!
Dialogue: 0,00:46:03.22,00:46:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck is \Ngoing on here?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:27.12,00:46:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Thank fucking God!</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:46:29.62,00:46:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck off!
Dialogue: 0,00:46:33.71,00:46:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Rubio, coming your way now. \NGotta swap out a bad sensor.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:41.63,00:46:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What was here versus \Nwhat was found.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:44.47,00:46:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it square?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:46.22,00:46:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty good. I mean, \Nthe morphine's gone,
Dialogue: 0,00:46:48.14,00:46:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's always the \Nfirst thing to go.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:51.60,00:46:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a bit weird, though.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:54.56,00:46:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"A predator restraint with \N42-inch offset jaws."
Dialogue: 0,00:46:58.15,00:47:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Six listed, zero found.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:01.07,00:47:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an odd thing \Nto go for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:03.78,00:47:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but, Boss, you know how shit \Ngoes missing from these stations.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:06.61,00:47:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,One bad year and guys are \Nripping shit off for salvage.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:18.17,00:47:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Santana?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:20.42,00:47:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You did sweep the area \Nbefore I got here, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:23.26,00:47:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweep for what?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:25.26,00:47:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I just want to make sure \Nno one has set any traps for us.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:47:27.55,00:47:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,5Q.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:31.76,00:47:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:33.56,00:47:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Traps? What kind of traps?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:36.19,00:47:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>The kind with jaws.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:47:44.90,00:47:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch that \Nfucking thing!
Dialogue: 0,00:47:53.04,00:47:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:58.25,00:47:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Up-armor.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:10.18,00:48:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,00:48:11.55,00:48:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready. Ready.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:16.14,00:48:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay put, \Nstay put, stay put, stay put!
Dialogue: 0,00:48:22.65,00:48:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oopah!
Dialogue: 0,00:48:28.53,00:48:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Who the hell was \Nthat screaming and why?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:48:33.08,00:48:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nunez, break out \Nthe sweep gear.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:37.41,00:48:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And figure out how many \Nof these big-ass traps
Dialogue: 0,00:48:40.92,00:48:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we got out here, okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:43.96,00:48:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking maybe the \Nwhole upper left quad
Dialogue: 0,00:48:46.46,00:48:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is some kind of \Nfucking mine field.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:49.34,00:48:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to do that \Nnow, okay, Nunez?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:53.60,00:48:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Copy that, Nunez?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:48:59.89,00:49:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nunez?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:03.52,00:49:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad. This is very bad.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:08.28,00:49:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nunez? Nunez?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:09.65,00:49:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Shut the fuck up, puto!</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:49:11.20,00:49:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,His radio just crapped out. \NSomeone get eyes on him.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:14.16,00:49:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Make sure he's right where he \Nshould be, 13-H. Go, go, go!</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:49:24.50,00:49:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:25.71,00:49:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,13-H. He's supposed to \Nbe right fucking...
Dialogue: 0,00:49:38.31,00:49:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mess with me now.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:42.52,00:49:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hey, what is it? \NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:43.69,00:49:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Get back! \N- It's me, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:44.98,00:49:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got Falco!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:55.24,00:49:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jock up, but you're \Nstaying home.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:58.37,00:50:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's going out \Nthere until I say so.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:01.37,00:50:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Man down, \Nhe's got Falco.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:02.67,00:50:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Compromise, compromise.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:03.96,00:50:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>How the fuck \Ndid he do that?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:05.00,00:50:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Never ever saw him, man. \NHe was right here and I never...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:07.04,00:50:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>What about the ship? \NIs he on it?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:08.17,00:50:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>He's not coming for the \Nships, he's coming for fucking us!</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:10.26,00:50:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Just fucking shoot! Shoot!</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:50:20.18,00:50:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One night, three dead.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:22.69,00:50:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not sure I'm \Nloving this trend.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:25.10,00:50:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Two dead, one missing.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:26.36,00:50:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Three dead.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:27.90,00:50:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, look at it \Nthis way, boys.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:32.90,00:50:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We might all fit \Non one ship now.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:34.86,00:50:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Diaz!
Dialogue: 0,00:50:40.62,00:50:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Get those other \Ntraps back there.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:43.12,00:50:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Luna, say something \NBible-like over these bodies.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:57.51,00:50:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, maybe,
Dialogue: 0,00:51:00.93,00:51:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we zero this out.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:04.85,00:51:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your tag anyway?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:06.94,00:51:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you wanna know my name.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:11.65,00:51:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not sure \NI'm gonna say.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:13.57,00:51:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everyone you know by \Nname, Santana, winds up dead.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:19.78,00:51:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You gonna clean this shit up?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:30.84,00:51:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me. \N- Wow.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:32.92,00:51:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out for \Nsurprise attacks.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:35.97,00:51:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:37.80,00:51:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's time to start \Nmerging assets, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:44.35,00:51:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is you \Nasking for my help?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:46.69,00:51:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is me saying that I may \Nneed some of your gear.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:51.82,00:51:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If some of your guys happen to \Ncome attached to that gear,
Dialogue: 0,00:51:56.28,00:52:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I will understand that's \Nthe way it's gotta be.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:01.78,00:52:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're asking for \Nmy gear's help?
Dialogue: 0,00:52:04.45,00:52:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,More like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:06.96,00:52:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Moss...
Dialogue: 0,00:52:15.30,00:52:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The gear's saying, \N"Nah." Bitch.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:18.63,00:52:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's your answer.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:20.18,00:52:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck do \Nyou want, man?
Dialogue: 0,00:52:22.47,00:52:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what? I'm gonna \Nfold you in, Santana.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:26.14,00:52:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I give orders to Dahl. And \NDelhi's gonna give orders to you.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:30.40,00:52:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the chain of command \Nfrom this point forward.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:33.82,00:52:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I not loving \Nthis plan so far?
Dialogue: 0,00:52:37.70,00:52:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know, I know. \NYou know why?
Dialogue: 0,00:52:40.49,00:52:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it sucks \Nass and swallows!
Dialogue: 0,00:52:43.49,00:52:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not taking orders \Nfrom your pet whore
Dialogue: 0,00:52:46.12,00:52:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who thinks I won't smack \Nher right back...
Dialogue: 0,00:52:50.33,00:52:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't fuck guys.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:53.00,00:52:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally I fuck 'em \Nup if they need it.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:58.17,00:53:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what's gonna happen, Santana. \NYou're gonna take a back seat.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:01.68,00:53:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll track Riddick \Ndown, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:04.05,00:53:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want him alive.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:06.02,00:53:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You give me a day, and after \Nthat he's yours to kill.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:10.52,00:53:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're giving me the bounty?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:12.35,00:53:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You pay my crew, fuel costs, the \Nrest is yours. That's the deal.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:18.03,00:53:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Riddick for you? \NNot just some convict.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:22.53,00:53:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want? \NWhy are you here?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:25.62,00:53:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:28.12,00:53:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Johns.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:29.75,00:53:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lock down those ships, \Nget those hogs on deck.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:32.17,00:53:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I will ride with \NMoss and Lockspur.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:34.17,00:53:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a non-lethal load-out, L.O.D.'s \Nand phosphor frags to start with.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:38.46,00:53:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a man that hunts by night. \NWe'll take it to him by day.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:43.72,00:53:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Diaz! Vargas! Show me the \Nspot of the last kill.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:50.39,00:53:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Some kind of canine.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:04.91,00:54:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Diaz, I got a dog here.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:07.87,00:54:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the same dingo-dongo \Nthing from last night?
Dialogue: 0,00:54:11.25,00:54:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, I'm pretty sure \Nwe killed that one.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:20.42,00:54:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be the same one.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:22.51,00:54:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The same.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:23.63,00:54:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dahl, get your sniper rifle \Nand barium rounds now.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:38.15,00:54:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,1,500 meters.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:52.47,00:55:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be just the first hole it found.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:55.10,00:55:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A stressed animal is gonna \Nrun to ground it knows.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:59.77,00:56:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I'm getting \Nhuman pheromones.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:25.98,00:57:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Riddick!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:34.62,00:57:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dial down, dial \Ndown, dial down!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:44.63,00:57:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Santana's guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:45.96,00:57:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Falco.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:47.09,00:57:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit. Did we \Njust kill a hostage?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:49.13,00:57:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been hunting \NRiddick for 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:51.13,00:57:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The concept of a hostage \Nhas no appeal to him.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:54.05,00:57:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Falco was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:56.43,00:57:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just some fucking \Nsideshow to buy more time.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:02.19,00:58:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Fuck...
Dialogue: 0,00:58:05.31,00:58:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:10.07,00:58:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just dropped some \Nmud right there.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:13.07,00:58:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Riddick isn't here...
Dialogue: 0,00:58:23.33,00:58:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, he could \Nbe anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:16.26,00:59:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>This is Johns to \Nany-goddamn-body at the station.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:59:19.22,00:59:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I want you to keep an eye on that \Nlocker. Keep an eye on the node.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:59:23.81,00:59:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Riddick may have \Nmade an end run.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:59:26.77,00:59:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>My ETA is seven minutes. \NBut watch your back.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:00:11.86,01:00:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to see this.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:22.33,01:00:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote that?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:24.54,01:00:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He took out our deep space \Ncommunications. All of it.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:28.71,01:00:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And whose blood is that? \NThere... Here...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:32.71,01:00:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:39.64,01:00:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to kick his ass again. \NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:43.76,01:00:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:52.94,01:00:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck it.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:55.44,01:00:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:09.71,01:01:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Six.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:11.67,01:01:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:15.50,01:01:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Six.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:18.84,01:01:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a shit storm trooper, \NSantana. I'll give you that.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:22.68,01:01:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You beat the devil this time.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:24.89,01:01:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't actually \Nthink he was gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:27.81,01:01:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a sign.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:30.69,01:01:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sweet.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:34.69,01:01:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe this is a sign.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:39.24,01:01:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be that the good Lord \Nwants us to take these nodes
Dialogue: 0,01:01:42.32,01:01:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and flee this planet \Njust as soon as we can.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:49.87,01:01:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my good luck charm.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:55.42,01:01:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong business, kid.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:58.34,01:02:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was kind of \Nhoping the bomb would go off.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:10.73,01:02:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we sealed up his cave with some \Nphosphor frags here, so he can't go back.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:15.40,01:02:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And just like an animal, he's \Ngonna head to known ground.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:18.44,01:02:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're gonna find he's got \Nthree or four lairs out there.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:21.53,01:02:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll radius out \Nfrom this point, here.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:24.95,01:02:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now radio comms... I saw three \Nrepeaters listed in inventory.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:28.87,01:02:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Find them. Set them up \Nat regular intervals.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:32.25,01:02:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I never want to be out of \Ntouch like that again.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:09.95,01:03:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you scared of me?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:13.91,01:03:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:19.09,01:03:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they scared of me?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:22.67,01:03:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they're scared of you.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:30.81,01:03:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're all scared \Nof the wrong thing.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:34.14,01:03:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lockspur, I want you to lock \Ndown those hogs, all right?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:36.48,01:03:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want this guy any more \Nmobile than he already is.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:39.73,01:03:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Dahl, I spotted a \Nnice little nest for you.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:42.48,01:03:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here and in \Nthese low hills.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:51.12,01:03:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Moss?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:55.71,01:03:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I just saw him.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:58.83,01:04:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Say again?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:01.29,01:04:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I just saw him.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:13.64,01:04:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dahl, I want you to \Nsit on this ship!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:15.31,01:04:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Diaz, make sure your \Nship is locked down!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:17.85,01:04:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of you get on \Nthe fucking perimeter
Dialogue: 0,01:04:19.94,01:04:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep your eyes \Non each other!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:21.98,01:04:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Santana! He got the \Nfucking nodes!
Dialogue: 0,01:05:13.12,01:05:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. It's coming.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:18.96,01:05:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we just combine nodes.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:20.62,01:05:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull one from that ship, put \Nit in this ship, you know?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:22.79,01:05:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Amps is amps, right?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:23.96,01:05:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about amps. It's about \NWhat each ship is rated to handle.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:26.71,01:05:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You miss by even a few milli-joules, \Nyou fry every chip you've got.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:29.47,01:05:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so figure out the \Ndifference, and just do it.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:31.93,01:05:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jailbreak the fucking thing.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:33.68,01:05:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I could give you \Na crash course
Dialogue: 0,01:05:35.60,01:05:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on thermodynamic equilibrium \Nand energy exchange right now,
Dialogue: 0,01:05:38.93,01:05:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe you just want to take \Nmy goddamn word for it...
Dialogue: 0,01:05:40.98,01:05:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it. I get it.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:42.44,01:05:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The ships are incompatible. We're not \Ngonna fly without the nodes back.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:45.48,01:05:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I feel like we just \Ncut off our own nuts here?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:47.61,01:05:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably because we did.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:49.28,01:05:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How about I take one of those jet \Nhogs, two days' worth of food
Dialogue: 0,01:05:51.82,01:05:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and go out and hunt this \Nfucker down myself?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:53.62,01:05:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad idea, Diaz. \NOne-on-one with Riddick?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:56.28,01:05:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I might be able to get the \Nemergency beacon working again.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:58.87,01:06:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's like an ambulance calling \Nfor an ambulance, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,01:06:01.37,01:06:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's back-up for the \Nfucking back-up. We can't.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:03.71,01:06:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought he was \Nthe one stranded here.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:05.42,01:06:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, looks \Nlike you thought wrong.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:07.34,01:06:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Long wait for back-up.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:06:11.38,01:06:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In case you were \Nthinking about
Dialogue: 0,01:06:12.76,01:06:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>fixing the beacon and \Ncalling for help.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:06:15.89,01:06:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Falco's radio.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:17.81,01:06:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Riddick, I don't give a \Nfuck about the back-up.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:21.85,01:06:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've still got \Nall kinds of gear
Dialogue: 0,01:06:23.52,01:06:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that can ruin your \Nday in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:27.40,01:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go find another \Nfucking cave.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:30.40,01:06:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep running, \Nyou keep hiding.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:33.57,01:06:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter me none.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:36.37,01:06:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the end, \NI will find you!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:41.83,01:06:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Look South.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:04.73,01:07:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:06.98,01:07:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The balls on this fucking guy.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:11.61,01:07:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dahl, keep an eye \Non things here.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:16.32,01:07:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,01:07:17.45,01:07:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay low.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:21.29,01:07:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:44.77,01:07:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of you drop.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:09.33,01:08:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the bounty at?
Dialogue: 0,01:08:11.67,01:08:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't care. \NIt's not why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:14.51,01:08:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet the big jamoke knows.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:17.01,01:08:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I know exactly \Nwhat it is.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:20.18,01:08:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What I do know is that it's double \Nif you're brought back dead.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:24.56,01:08:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's new.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:27.52,01:08:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it be enough to \Npay for your funerals?
Dialogue: 0,01:08:32.07,01:08:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm interested in
Dialogue: 0,01:08:34.36,01:08:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is a little backwater place \Nwith a system code M-344/G.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:39.70,01:08:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what happened \Nthere 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:45.54,01:08:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The father.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:50.88,01:08:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Daddy Johns.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:52.34,01:08:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:54.00,01:08:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you traveled all \Nthis way just to see me.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:59.97,01:09:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm flattered.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:01.76,01:09:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of strange \Nnot knowing
Dialogue: 0,01:09:02.89,01:09:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what to put down in \Nthe family Bible.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:05.10,01:09:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of strange three guys have \Nto die just so that you can hear...
Dialogue: 0,01:09:08.27,01:09:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. You don't get \Nto put that shit on me.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:11.65,01:09:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Those kills are on you.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:13.69,01:09:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling that's not the \Nonly thing on me right now.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:17.61,01:09:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got barium shells, \Nstab-shock, explosive tip.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:20.57,01:09:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want, \Nbarium or stab-shock?
Dialogue: 0,01:09:23.28,01:09:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Horse tranq.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:25.45,01:09:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:31.75,01:09:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to interrupt this \Ndiscussion about ancient history,
Dialogue: 0,01:09:35.34,01:09:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but maybe I should step in right \Nhere and introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:38.72,01:09:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- My name is... \N- Box Boy.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:42.72,01:09:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Say What?
Dialogue: 0,01:09:44.26,01:09:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the guy who said that he was \Ngonna put my head in a box. Right?
Dialogue: 0,01:09:49.85,01:09:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was me \Nspitting noise.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:55.40,01:09:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But you do have a box.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:57.40,01:09:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have a box?
Dialogue: 0,01:09:59.32,01:10:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thought I saw one.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:02.61,01:10:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, of course I've got a box. \NEveryone's got a box, man.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:06.16,01:10:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Diaz has a \Nfucking huge box.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:09.79,01:10:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:12.08,01:10:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna use it.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:17.63,01:10:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Three down, eight left.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:20.63,01:10:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, normally I'd \Njust keep going.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:23.13,01:10:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Six down... Nine down...
Dialogue: 0,01:10:27.64,01:10:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You get where I'm \Ngoing with this.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:30.93,01:10:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But things are changing here
Dialogue: 0,01:10:32.69,01:10:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and nobody wants to be on this \Nplanet 24 hours from now.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:37.44,01:10:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I suggest we make it work.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:40.15,01:10:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want, a \Ngentleman's agreement?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:42.24,01:10:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave one node out \Nin the open. You take it.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:45.62,01:10:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The other node and the \Nother ship are mine.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:49.49,01:10:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:50.75,01:10:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we playing here, \Nretard bingo? What?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:55.54,01:10:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That was on the table \Nfrom the start...
Dialogue: 0,01:10:57.54,01:10:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget the start.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:01.55,01:11:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the end you want \Nto think about now.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:06.89,01:11:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See that?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:12.23,01:11:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you till that \Nrain hits that station.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:17.56,01:11:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your clock.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:26.95,01:11:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"Box Boy"...
Dialogue: 0,01:11:38.38,01:11:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dahl! Do it now! Now!
Dialogue: 0,01:11:56.85,01:11:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Again!
Dialogue: 0,01:12:04.15,01:12:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not going down.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:07.57,01:12:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it again, Dahl!
Dialogue: 0,01:12:14.37,01:12:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go down.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:37.69,01:12:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this, Dahl.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:13.55,01:13:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Riddick.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:15.06,01:13:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Riddick?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:25.65,01:13:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Johns?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:30.20,01:13:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We beating men in chains now?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:39.08,01:13:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, from the beginning. \NFor the historical record...
Dialogue: 0,01:13:43.67,01:13:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>The Hunter Gratzner.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:13:44.79,01:13:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the commercial \Nvessel my son uses
Dialogue: 0,01:13:46.25,01:13:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to transport you \Nback to the slammer.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:47.63,01:13:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But that ship sends a distress \Ncall somewhere near M-344/G.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:52.55,01:13:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a backwater system, with \Ntwo suns, one habitable planet.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:58.31,01:14:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he survive the crash?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:01.52,01:14:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Big drama the next few hours.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:04.65,01:14:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever happens, no \Nmatter what they tell you,
Dialogue: 0,01:14:10.82,01:14:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,don't let 'em take \Nthese chains off me.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:13.78,01:14:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Them? Who's "them"? Who \Nare you talking...
Dialogue: 0,01:14:15.83,01:14:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know who you're \Ntalking to here?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:22.29,01:14:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That was for me?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:26.96,01:14:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For the historical record,
Dialogue: 0,01:14:30.84,01:14:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he made it.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:38.35,01:14:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's just you and him?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:41.31,01:14:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Was, uh,
Dialogue: 0,01:14:43.73,01:14:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about the same number you \Nsee here in this room.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:48.11,01:14:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So how many made it off?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:50.82,01:14:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Three.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:53.57,01:14:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But not him?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:56.87,01:14:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:58.74,01:15:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So between the time of the crash and \Nthe time you leave that planet,
Dialogue: 0,01:15:02.08,01:15:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,my son dies.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:04.92,01:15:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can safely assume it's \Nat your hands. Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,01:15:12.34,01:15:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what you see \Noutside that window, Dahl.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:13.93,01:15:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what you see \Noutside that window, Dahl.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:29.69,01:15:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Cyclops unit, two ships,
Dialogue: 0,01:15:32.28,01:15:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,couple dead guys in plastic.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:35.20,01:15:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't see anything else?
Dialogue: 0,01:15:37.11,01:15:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:56.63,01:15:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Time's up.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:04.39,01:16:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is up.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:07.56,01:16:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:16.24,01:16:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold him down.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:52.44,01:16:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,More dingo-dongos maybe.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:58.65,01:16:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:03.33,01:17:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what's coming.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:06.58,01:17:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Called to find you. \NThe serpents...
Dialogue: 0,01:17:31.15,01:17:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,spotlight!
Dialogue: 0,01:17:59.51,01:18:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said,
Dialogue: 0,01:18:02.26,01:18:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it ain't me you \Ngotta worry about.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:09.27,01:18:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? What's out there?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:11.94,01:18:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:14.27,01:18:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Fucked up or \Nsomething out there.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:16.40,01:18:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It ain't right. \NIt's coming our way.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:28.87,01:18:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever they are, they \Nain't so hard to kill.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:12.08,01:19:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck?
Dialogue: 0,01:19:35.52,01:19:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,01:19:51.12,01:19:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No more holes, please.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:14.89,01:20:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck is happening? \NHow fucked are we?
Dialogue: 0,01:20:18.35,01:20:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows how long \Nit will rain?
Dialogue: 0,01:20:22.36,01:20:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Or just how many of them \Nare buried out there?
Dialogue: 0,01:20:28.57,01:20:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw it. He saw it with those eyes \Nof his and he didn't tell us what.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:42.63,01:20:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One ship for you, one for me.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:46.63,01:20:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to know that these \Nnodes are retrievable.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:51.39,01:20:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I need to know \Nwe have a deal.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:58.27,01:20:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a deal.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:07.24,01:21:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The chains stay on.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:22.71,01:21:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we sit this one out?
Dialogue: 0,01:21:27.63,01:21:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:30.59,01:21:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Up, up, up...
Dialogue: 0,01:21:35.56,01:21:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Good doggie.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:01.83,01:22:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,01:22:03.88,01:22:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy shit.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:58.72,01:23:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the hell did that... Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,01:23:02.81,01:23:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,01:23:06.73,01:23:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck is wrong with \Nyou, you crazy bastard?
Dialogue: 0,01:23:09.53,01:23:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have killed me!
Dialogue: 0,01:23:10.86,01:23:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,01:23:20.74,01:23:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Vargas, get up.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:23.16,01:23:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Vargas, get up. \NCome on, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:25.62,01:23:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Vargas, come on, man. \NWalk it off.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:27.33,01:23:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. It's \Njust a little one.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:29.25,01:23:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Small ones are the worst.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:32.76,01:23:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They save the most venom.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:55.32,01:23:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to mention,
Dialogue: 0,01:23:58.70,01:24:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no weapons for you.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:07.33,01:24:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you can ride \None of these things?
Dialogue: 0,01:24:09.88,01:24:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ride it like I stole it.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:26.52,01:24:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take flank.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:39.03,01:24:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If Riddick comes back \Nhere without us,
Dialogue: 0,01:24:41.33,01:24:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you go ahead, you kill him \Non general principle.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:44.66,01:24:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that before or after \NI'm supposed to fuck him?
Dialogue: 0,01:27:22.44,01:27:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How bad you want \Nthose nodes, Johns?
Dialogue: 0,01:28:01.11,01:28:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose you took the \Ntime to do this for him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,01:28:06.57,01:28:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This may come as a \Nshock to you, Johns,
Dialogue: 0,01:28:10.74,01:28:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn't ghost your son.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:14.83,01:28:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He seemed set on \Nkilling himself.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:20.79,01:28:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,01:28:23.42,01:28:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Morphine.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:26.43,01:28:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your son liked his morphine.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:29.34,01:28:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Liked it twice a day.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:32.14,01:28:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't know your \Nson was a junkie?
Dialogue: 0,01:28:38.15,01:28:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Johns was like most Mercs.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:40.86,01:28:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They look all \Nstand-up and do-right
Dialogue: 0,01:28:44.86,01:28:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,until you out them open and \Nyou find something missing.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:48.70,01:28:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In his case, a spine.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:52.45,01:28:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to listen to this \Nshit! That's not the man I knew.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:56.04,01:28:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you didn't know your son.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:03.50,01:29:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to kill a kid.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:07.22,01:29:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To save his own skin.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:09.63,01:29:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:13.06,01:29:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You expect me to believe
Dialogue: 0,01:29:15.56,01:29:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,my son was gonna kill a \Nchild to save his own life?
Dialogue: 0,01:29:21.02,01:29:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Morphine makes the \Nbrain soft. Heart weak.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:28.40,01:29:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't fucking buy it!
Dialogue: 0,01:29:30.82,01:29:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't believe that \Nmy son's the bad guy
Dialogue: 0,01:29:33.08,01:29:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in this fucking demented \Nfairy tale of yours.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:39.04,01:29:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No reason to lie now.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:43.88,01:29:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Johns.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:48.30,01:29:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Either one of us.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:19.08,01:30:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for starting the killing \Nspree for me, Riddick.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:21.62,01:30:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll take it from here.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:16.14,01:31:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jamoke.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:22.43,01:31:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So that blade you buried \Nwas meant for me?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:26.86,01:31:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who deserved \Nit, really.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:32.74,01:31:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a problem, Riddick,
Dialogue: 0,01:31:36.03,01:31:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've got \Ntwo nodes here.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:38.70,01:31:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got one hog.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:40.70,01:31:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I sure as shit am not \Nriding bitch with you again.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:47.08,01:31:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One hog?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:49.88,01:31:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure about that, Johns?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:57.59,01:32:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He pulled the goddamn \Nturbine pin!
Dialogue: 0,01:32:01.64,01:32:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You just figured that out?
Dialogue: 0,01:32:04.27,01:32:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Diaz was gonna take the nodes \Nfor himself and ghost me.
Dialogue: 0,01:32:08.23,01:32:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He was gonna leave \Nyou out here alone.
Dialogue: 0,01:32:11.40,01:32:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So what now?
Dialogue: 0,01:32:20.28,01:32:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we switch to \Nour ground game.
Dialogue: 0,01:32:24.25,01:32:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that lack of \Nspine runs in the family.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:19.63,01:33:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Reload!
Dialogue: 0,01:33:27.18,01:33:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch your head.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:39.24,01:33:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,01:35:43.61,01:35:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I got inbound.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:00.04,01:36:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,01:36:01.96,01:36:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it just you?
Dialogue: 0,01:36:04.59,01:36:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just slam this thing in. \NSee if it's still good.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:10.31,01:36:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss...
Dialogue: 0,01:36:11.39,01:36:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just see if the fucking thing \Nworks! We need to get outta here.
Dialogue: 0,01:40:19.26,01:40:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraction, 30 seconds or less. \NLet's go, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,01:41:35.30,01:41:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Lot of good \Nmen died here, Riddick.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:41:37.55,01:41:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Not sure how I'm supposed to \Noverlook that. Next time.
Dialogue: 0,01:41:41.84,01:41:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Things would \Nhave been different
Dialogue: 0,01:41:43.97,01:41:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if they weren't trying \Nto put my head in a box.
Dialogue: 0,01:41:49.02,01:41:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So where to now, Riddick?
Dialogue: 0,01:41:51.73,01:41:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what? Fuck that. \NDon't tell me. I don't wanna know.
Dialogue: 0,01:41:56.48,01:41:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I'll tell you this, Johns.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:41:58.86,01:42:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Sooner or later, we all \Nhave to head home.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:42:03.07,01:42:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Tell Dahl to keep \Nit warm for me.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:42:06.08,01:42:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And, Johns,
Dialogue: 0,01:42:08.83,01:42:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you keep a strong spine.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:58.30,01:42:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Vaako.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:02.30,01:43:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- You are still alive. \N- Tell me where.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:06.89,01:43:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's no longer among us.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:08.81,01:43:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, and I'll \Nkill him first.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:12.39,01:43:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You misunderstand.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:14.19,01:43:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Vaako is a decent man who \Nmeant to honor his word.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:17.73,01:43:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with you, strangely.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:19.90,01:43:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about Furya.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:21.65,01:43:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what the pact \Nwas between you and him.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:24.32,01:43:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This faith cannot \Nhave a misbeliever
Dialogue: 0,01:43:26.70,01:43:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or a kind heart leading it,
Dialogue: 0,01:43:28.24,01:43:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have done what I have \Ndone to ensure...
Dialogue: 0,01:43:41.26,01:43:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many words.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:57.86,01:44:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Never lie to me, \NI'll never hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:03.90,01:44:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One word answer.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:07.74,01:44:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Vaako alive or dead?
Dialogue: 0,01:44:14.75,01:44:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Both.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:38.90,01:44:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Transcendence.</i>
